# Vanity redirects.
/dashboard       /             301
/analytics       /             301
/index.htm       /             301

# SPA fallback for per-tab linkable URLs (/nse-stocks, /bse-stocks,
# /cross-exchange, /market-changes, /overview): rewrite any unmatched
# path to index.html so direct links + browser refresh stay on the
# right tab. The dashboard JS reads location.pathname at boot and
# activates the matching tab (unknown paths fall back to Overview).
#
# Why a wildcard and not five explicit /path -> /index.html 200 rules:
# Cloudflare Pages treats literal-destination 200 rewrites on non-
# wildcard sources as redirects (issues a 308 to /). The /* form is
# the documented SPA pattern that actually rewrites.
#
# Real files (sitemap.xml, robots.txt, /compressed_data/*, *.json,
# *.gz, *.html, etc.) are served by Cloudflare BEFORE _redirects is
# consulted, so this catch-all only fires for paths with no on-disk
# asset.
/*               /index.html   200
